]] were locked down. Authorities in [[Nilgiris]] district ordered the closure of tourist sites including [[Ooty]] and the tourists staying in hotels and resorts were given 24 hours to leave the city.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus: Tourist centres in TN under lockdown; Visitors in| url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/coronavirus-tourist-centres-in-tn-under-lockdown-visitors-in/1768933|website=outlookindia|author=}}</ref> In [[Maharashtra]], government offices were closed down for seven days.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus Outbreak: Maharashtra to shut government offices for next 7 days| url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/news/india/coronavirus-uddhav-thackeray-maharashtra-government-offices-shut-7-days-598998|website=indiatv|author=| date=17 March 2020}}</ref> [[Chandigarh]] administration ordered the closure of shopping malls, cinema halls, gyms, nightclubs, swimming pools, coaching centres, spas, creches and video game parlours till 31 March. It also banned gatherings of more than a 100 people and census work was postponed.<ref>{{cite web |title=Covid-19: Malls, cinema halls, gyms closed in Chandigarh| url=https://m.hindustantimes.com/cities/malls-clubs-discotheques-and-gyms-closed-in-chandigarh-till-march-31-to-check-coronavirus-spread/story-SlWceuV22oQXG5RKxODz4M.html|website=Hindustan times|author=| date=16 March 2020}}</ref> At the same time, [[Dera]] chiefs were asked to postpone all religious events till 31 March.<ref>{{cite news |title=Punjab malls, gyms, restaurants deserted after advisory on coronavirus| url=https://wap.business-standard.com/multimedia/video-gallery/general/punjab-malls-gyms-restaurants-deserted-after-advisory-on-coronavirus-101227.htm|newspaper=Business Standard India|author=}}</ref> The GoM has also directed that no more than 50 people are allowed to gather at any place other than [[weddings]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Punjab: Malls, shopping complexes shut till March 31; curbs on gatherings at marriage palaces| url=https://www.