ive|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=23 March 2020}}</ref> At 6 am on 23 March Delhi was put under lockdown till at least 31 March. Essential services and commodities were to continue.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Jagannath |first1=J. |title=Delhi lockdown to start at 6 am Monday, until 31 March: Kejriwal |url=https://www.livemint.com/news/india/delhi-lockdown-to-start-at-6-am-monday-until-31-march-kejriwal-11584881955813.html |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=Livemint |date=22 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/kolkata/lockdown-in-west-bengal-from-5pm-today-government-to-shut-down-non-essentials/articleshow/74766599.cms|title=Lockdown in West Bengal: From 5pm today, government to shut down non-essentials|date=23 March 2020|work=The Times of India|accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref> 80 cities including major cities such as Bengaluru, Chennai, Mumbai,<ref>{{cite news |last1=Marpakwar |first1=Prafulla |title=Poor public response pushed govt to declare lockdown in Mumbai |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/mumbai/poor-public-response-pushed-govt-to-declare-lockdown-in-mumbai/articleshow/74766049.cms |accessdate=23 March 2020 |work=The Times of India |date=23 March 2020}}</ref> Chandigarh<ref>{{cite news |title=Chandigarh orders lock down till March 31 |url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/chandigarh-orders-lock-down-till-march-31/article31135191.ece |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=The Hindu |date=23 March 2020}}</ref> and Kolkata were also put under lockdown.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Gunasekar |first1=Arvind |last2=Bhattacharji |first2=Chetan |title=Coronavirus: 80 Cities Across India Go Into Lockdown Till March 31. What It Means |url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/coronavirus-covid-19-80-cities-across-india-go-into-lockdown-till-march-31-what-it-means-2198894 |accessdate=23 March 2020 |work=NDTV |date=23 March 2020}}</ref> Inter-state movements are allowed during the lockdown period. However some states have closed their borders.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/coronavirus-outbreak-lockdown-in-delhi-uttar-pradesh-rajasthan-telangana-andhra-nagaland-full-details-1658523-2020-03-22|title=Coronavirus outbreak: States impose lockdown in battle against Covid-19 {{!}} All you need to know|date=|website=India Today|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=23 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 23 March, [[Government of India|union]] and [[State government in india|state governments]] announced the lockdown of 75 districts where cases were reported.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus update: 75 cities across India under lockdown. Full list across states| url=https://www.livemint.com/news/india/coronavirus-update-75-cities-across-india-under-lockdown-full-list-across-states-11584931492672.html|website=Livemint|author=| date=23 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March, [[Prime Minister of India|PM]] [[Narendra Modi]] announced a complete nationwide lockdown, starting from midnight for 21 days.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.firstpost.com/health/narendra-modi-on-coronavirus-speech-live-updates-streaming-watch-india-pm-address-to-nation-on-covid-19-today-latest-news-lockdown-janata-curfew-8182241.html|title=Narendra Modi on Coronavirus Outbreak LIVE Updates: India under complete shutdown for 21 days starting 12 pm tonight, says PM|date=|work=Firstpost|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 6 April, In Telangana, CM suggested that the Lockdown should be extended by two weeks after April 14.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.in/india/news/lockdown-in-telangana-extended-till-june-3/articleshow/75014509.cms|title=Telangana CM suggests lockdown extension by two weeks|date=|website=Business Insder|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date= 6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 April, The Yogi government has ordered the hot spot areas of 15 districts of [[Uttar Pradesh]] to be completely sealed till April 15.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.timesnownews.com/india/article/up-15-district-name-uttar-pradesh-lockdown-latest-news-15-districts-sealed-list-and-what-it-means/575560t|date=|website=Timesnownews|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date= 8 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 April, the [[Government of Odisha]] extended the Lockdown in the state till April 30.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/odisha-becomes-first-state-to-extend-covid-19-lockdown-sets-april-30-as-new-date/story-MLEr0Zie3fXZWufT1lC2QM.html|title=Odisha becomes first state to extend Covid-19 lockdown; sets April 30 as new date|date=2020-04-09|website=Hindustan Times|language=en|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref>\n\n===Evacuations===\n[[File:Minister visiting the Coronavirus Quarantine Centre 2.jpg|thumb|The Minister of State for Home Affairs, [[Nityanand Rai]] visiting evacuees at the Coronavirus Quarantine Centre, after completion of their requisite quarantine period, at the ITBP Chhawla Centre, in New Delhi on 13 March 2020.]]\nThe [[Ministry of External Affairs (India)|Ministry of External Affairs]] under [[Minister of External Affairs (India)|Minister]] [[Subrahmanyam Jaishankar]], [[Air India]] and the [[Indian Air Force]] have been successful in evacuating many Indian nationals and certain foreign nationals from the virus effected areas.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/news/india/coronavirus-special-flights-land-in-delhi-after-evacuation-from-japan-china-11582773171379.html|title=Coronavirus: Special flights land in Delhi after evacuation from Japan, China|first=Elizabeth|last=Roche|date=27 February 2020|website=Livemint|access-date=5 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228151542/https://www.livemint.com/news/india/coronavirus-special-flights-land-in-delhi-after-evacuation-from-japan-china-11582773171379.html|archive-date=28 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-n